A jet of flames burst from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set a specific part of the forest ablaze, then circled overhead, observing it for a while. Strangely, as he had slowed down, the odd noises and cries behind him had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't get suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's not so unpleasant, is it, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly disagreed with Nyssi; he seemed less black than usual and had dug his claws into Thassalin's back so deeply that he had drawn blood from the Thraki. However, evidently, he didn't care much about it. That said, Thassalin had realized he had frightened his new friends and had found a clearing to land in.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SMELLED SOMETHING. I HAD TO CHECK."
"You had to drag us all the way here with you?" Tenuk exclaimed as he slid down from Thassalin's back along her tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our great and strong warrior! How is he ever going to join us?"
"I'll find a way," retorted Nissy. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive anything like Kayel's cute little car either. And if he started coming to work by car, it's only because YOU drive us there. He just has that bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly hilarious, and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him a little too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR GREAT FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A TINY BIKE MEANT FOR KIDS TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WOULD HAVE WANTED TO BE TALENTED IN TELEPATHY. THAT'S A PRECIOUS THOUGHT! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel snickered, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up, and why did you fly away so quickly?"
Thassalin grumbled, took off, and vanished briefly before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a golden and white dragon-like creature, very rare. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR WAILS. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDED. THE CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel did as well, their attention drawn by a break in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, the creature spread two colossal pairs of wings and rushed straight toward Thassalin, unbothered by the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk barely managed to take cover, but Nyssi was dragged along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nissy and throwing her onto his back, using his extraordinary long and dexterous tail, before taking off. The two-winged black creature quickly rushed after them.
Kayel exhaled as he drew the rifle from his back, then opened a pouch in which there was a ammunition belt. He slung it over his shoulder to be able to access it easily, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to transform into something that flies?" asked Kayel.
"Do you want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And what then? I have an ultra-powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to be used. I only need to see him to shoot him."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make some space. With a faint, slightly pained growl, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly returned to being a normal light blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb."
Having regained a more normal appearance of Thraki, Tenuk now had his back covered in scales, but a pair of spines had also grown on it, handy for Kayel to grip. Tenuk needed a bit of time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid it.
I suppose that's the other big scary monster that was scaring Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow while trying to shoot the second creature, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk did not react. He was too focused on his flight toward Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature chasing them. Kayel clumsily turned around to face the monster. The fact that it was pursuing them was a blessing for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, causing it to scream in pain before disappearing once again beneath the trees. Kayel did not know if it was still following them, but it certainly would not be able to catch up.
Further ahead, Nyssi was desperately clinging on while Thassalin circled overhead, firing bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it appeared furious and determined to fight on, and the fireballs didn't seem to be having the intended effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi seized the opportunity to draw his weapon, a reliable rifle. It certainly wasn't designed for situations like this, but a volley of shots would surely at least discourage the black beast, right?
